PROJECT: Student Management System

FOLDER STRUCTURE
backend/
  app/
    api/
      v1/
        students.py
        courses.py
        enrollments.py
    services/
        student_service.py
        course_service.py
        enrollment_service.py
    repositories/
        student_repository.py
        course_repository.py
        enrollment_repository.py
    models/
        student.py
        course.py
        enrollment.py
    schemas/
        student_schema.py
        course_schema.py
        enrollment_schema.py
    core/
        config.py
        database.py
        exceptions.py
        responses.py
    main.py

frontend/
  src/
    components/
    pages/
    services/
    App.jsx
    main.jsx


NAMING CONVENTIONS
Python files use snake_case.
React components use PascalCase.
SQLAlchemy models use singular names with no suffix (Student, Course, Enrollment).
Pydantic schemas must end with Schema (StudentCreateSchema, StudentResponseSchema).
API route files must use plural resource names (students.py, courses.py).


API RESPONSE FORMAT
All API endpoints must return the standardized response envelope.

Success response format:
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "message": "operation successful",
  "meta": {}
}

Error response format:
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "human readable message",
    "field": null
  }
}


ERROR HANDLING RULES
Never expose raw SQLAlchemy or internal exceptions to the API layer.
Use custom exceptions defined in core/exceptions.py.
All API errors must return the standardized error envelope.
Use explicit error codes such as STUDENT_NOT_FOUND, COURSE_NOT_FOUND, VALIDATION_ERROR.


LOGGING RULES
INFO level logging:
- Incoming API requests
- Successful operations (create, update, delete)

ERROR level logging:
- Unhandled exceptions
- Database failures
- Validation errors that indicate system misuse

Never log:
- passwords
- authentication tokens
- personally identifiable information (PII)


VALIDATION RULES
All request bodies must be validated using Pydantic schemas.
Email fields must use EmailStr validation.
All IDs must be validated as UUID.
Required fields must be enforced at schema level.


ASYNC REQUIREMENTS
All FastAPI route handlers must be asynchronous.
Database interactions must use async-compatible sessions.
Blocking operations must not run inside async routes.


FILE SIZE LIMIT
No single source file may exceed 200 lines.
If a file approaches this limit, split logic into additional modules.


TEST REQUIREMENTS
Every service function must have a corresponding unit test.
Service layer tests must mock repository interactions.
Tests must verify:
- successful operations
- validation failures
- permission failures
- not-found errors